<h3 id="7">Is it possible to buy EOS anonymously?</h3>
<p>Holders of EOS tokens are not anonymous online. Therefore, EOS tokens cannot be used anonymously.&nbsp;Even if you would only like to keep them in a wallet, anonymity cannot be achieved. The reason for this is that all major online exchanges and brokers require some form of identification verification prior to allowing users to use their services and acquire tokens in the first place.</p>
<h4 id="8">Is it possible to purchase EOS using PayPal, credit card, etc.?</h4>
<p>Yes, this is possible.&nbsp;A number of brokers allow you to deposit via credit/debit card, Sofort&uuml;berweisung, Neteller, PayPal, Skrill, or other payment methods. EOS Coins are then purchased with the topped-up credit. Additionally, PayPal's platform enables users to transfer cryptocurrency to third-party wallets.</p>
<h4 id="9">EOS wallets: which ones are available?</h4>
<p>Cryptocurrencies such as EOS can only be purchased and held directly through a crypto wallet. Hardware wallets provide the greatest protection against cyber-attacks. A multi-asset wallet may also be useful when trading several cryptocurrencies.&nbsp;As well as software wallets connected to the Internet, there are also paper wallets.</p>
<p>EOS runs on the Ethereum blockchain, so any wallet compatible with Ethereum or ERC20 tokens will be able to handle it. Listed below are some digital wallets where EOS can be stored.</p>
<h4 id="10">Ledger or Trezor</h4>
<p>In this context, we are discussing encrypted hardware wallets that utilize very high-quality encryption techniques to prevent the cryptocurrencies from being compromised by sophisticated network attacks or by simple phishing scams. Additionally, they enable the recovery of coins through a mnemonic seed phrase in the event the wallet is stolen, damaged or compromised.</p>
<h4 id="11">Trust Wallet</h4>
<p>Binance officially supports this wallet and it is one of the most popular among traders and investors. Security, convenience, and backup options are all provided by the software wallet.</p>
<h4 id="12">Atomic Wallet</h4>
<p>The wallet, which is compatible with Android, iOS, and several desktop platforms, supports more than 300 cryptocurrencies and includes a built-in exchange that allows users to exchange all supported assets, including EOS.</p>
<h4 id="13">MyEtherWallet</h4>
<p>The service provides traders and investors with a web-based solution that enables them to log in from anywhere. To access your money, one can choose from a variety of sign-up methods. To access your money, one can choose from a variety of sign-up methods.</p>
<h4 id="14">How does EOS mining work?</h4>
<p>EOS is not mined like Bitcoin. Tokens cannot be obtained by mining, they must be purchased directly.&nbsp;The EOS cryptocurrency has innovative features, which makes the purchase of EOS.&nbsp;IO makes it very interesting for investors.&nbsp;EOS pursues&nbsp;similar goals as the Ethereum network.&nbsp;You should take a close look at both of these cryptocurrencies if you wish to buy altcoins.</p>
